Package: perfectPeak
Type: Package
Title: Calculates the perfect peaks
Version: 0.3
Date: 2016-01-27
Author: Chris Reudenbach
Maintainer: Chris Reudenbach <creuden@gmail.com>
Description: perfectPeak is a package that combines the results of the Adavenced
    GIS course Marburg Geography. It provides the basic functions for calculating
    the parameters of dominance, prominence to determine the independence
    value of an peak. Furthermore there it contains functionality to initialise
    the R bindings to GRASS, SAGA and GDAL. The package has some aaditionally
    functionality in reading and using external data as Harrys Berliste and OSM data
    to derive the names of the peaks for Output. Finally ther is functionallity for
    simple webmapping of the results.
Sources: Marburg Open Courseware Advanced GIS: http://
    moc.environmentalinformatics-marburg.de/doku.php?id=courses:msc:advanced-
    gis:description Rauch. C. (2012): Der perfekte Gipfel.Panorama,2/2012,S.
    112 http://www.alpenverein.de/dav-services/panorama-magazin/dominanz-
    prominenz-eigenstaendigkeit-eines-berges_aid_11186.html Leonhard, W. (2012):
    Eigenstaendigkeit von Gipfeln.
License: GPL (>= 2)
Depends:
    R (>= 2.14),sp,raster,gdalUtils,RSAGA,rgrass7
RoxygenNote: 5.0.1
